Looking at the balance sheet, "Accounts Receivable" represents money owed to the company by customers who purchased goods or services on credit.

From the balance sheet:
- Accounts Receivable initial amount (2023-12-31): 0.00
- Accounts Receivable end amount (2024-02-03): 248540.09

These values represent the amounts owed to the entity for goods or services sold on credit at the beginning and end of the reporting period.
